    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-11-23T09:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-11-23T09:35:00-05:00" n="355"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d355">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.77/706: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-11-23T18:00:00+03:25"
                            >November 23, 1942—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 24—11:47 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>398. British Legation is seeking authority from Minister of State Cairo.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>(1)</label>
                    <item>To notify Iran Government formally that American military authorities are
                        taking over operation southern section Trans-Iranian railway and</item>
                    <label>(2)</label>
                    <item>After official notification is given to make public statement of this
                        fact, stating also that allocation of traffic on railway will continue to be
                        effected by British personnel.</item>
                </list>
                <p>Colonel Yount and I agree that official notification should be given Iranian
                    Government since our military authorities will soon have to carry on certain
                    negotiations with Iranian Government in this regard. However, we both feel that
                    a public statement at this time would serve no purpose and might even be harmful
                    since our personnel <pb facs="0327" n="315" xml:id="pg_315"/> are now on the
                    high seas. I should appreciate Department’s instructions and in meantime will
                    not agree to any public statement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
